# Coverage thresholds

## Global thresholds

Configured in root `vitest.config.ts`:

| Metric | Threshold | Enforcement |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| Lines | 80% | Hard fail in CI |
| Statements | 80% | Hard fail in CI |
| Functions | 70% | Hard fail in CI |
| Branches | 75% | Hard fail in CI |

## Per-package expectations

| Package type | Key coverage area |
|-------------|-------------------|
| Store plugins | Store initialization, state mutations, method calls, cross-store interactions |
| Magic plugins | Return value correctness, SSR safety, option normalization |
| Headless controllers | State machine transitions, event emission, cleanup |
| Query adapters | Reactivity bridge, stale handling, GC |

## Enforcement

```bash
pnpm run test:coverage      # vitest with coverage thresholds
```

## Rules

- Every behavior change MUST include tests.
- Global thresholds MUST NOT be lowered.
- New packages MUST meet minimum thresholds before first publish.
- Coverage exclusions MUST be documented in `vitest.config.ts` with rationale.
